We changed the schedule and manually the permission scan.

TextBody:
Hey Ryan,

Thank you for meeting with us today. To recap our session, we:

	Found the below error on both FSAA System Scan and Bulk Import:
	
		code = Constraint (19), message = System.Data.SQLite.SQLiteException (0x800027AF): constraint failed
		UNIQUE constraint failed: TBL_FSAA_ResourceMap.AccessID
		  at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.Util.RunInBackground[TResult](Action statusAction, Func`1 execAction)
		  at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.Util.RunInBackground(Action statusAction, Action execAction)
		  at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.BulkImportTask.InternalProcessRecord()
		  at Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.Tasks.Task.StartExecute()
		Corrected the above error by running the "Reset Hosts" option from FSAA > Query Settings > Maintenance > Reset Hosts
	
	
	Saw the Shares and ACLs repopulated in the AIC
	Added the StealthBITS service account to the Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access group
	
		This corrected users not being able to login and view Published Reports (Ticket #00426441) and incorrect properties count in the AD Summary report
	
	
	Began configuring the FileSystem > Ad Hoc Audits > FS_ShareAudit to output a report of ACLs per share
	
		
	
	


I'm going to go ahead and close out this ticket (#0042667) since we are able to see the ACLs in the AIC and via the new FS_ShareAudit report. I'm also going to close out ticket #00426441 | Cannot access Reporting since we resolved that issue as well. Ticket #00417261 will remain open while we continue to troubleshoot and investigate the issue with Admin users not being able to log into the AIC.

Thank you.

Tay Caliguiri

Senior Technical Support Engineer

www.netwrix.com
